DOCUMENT();
loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "Dartmouthmacros.pl");
 

## Do NOT show partial correct answers
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

## Lots of set up goes here
$r = random(1,20);

## Ok, we are ready to begin the problem...
##
TEXT(beginproblem());


BEGIN_TEXT
$BR

Find the absolute maximum and minimum of the function \( f(x,y) = x^2 - y^2
\) subject to the constraint \(x^2 + y^2 = \{$r*$r\} \).

As usual, ignore unneeded answer blanks, and list points in
lexicographic order.

Absolute minimum value: \{ans_rule()\}$BR
attained at (\{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\}) and  (\{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\}).

Absolute maximum value: \{ans_rule()\}$BR
attained at (\{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\}) and  (\{ans_rule(10)\}, \{ans_rule(10)\}).

$PAR
END_TEXT
# Minimum
ANS(num_cmp(- $r*$r));
ANS(num_cmp(0));
ANS(num_cmp(- $r));
ANS(num_cmp(0));
ANS(num_cmp($r));

# Maximum
ANS(num_cmp($r*$r));
ANS(num_cmp(- $r));
ANS(num_cmp(0));
ANS(num_cmp($r));
ANS(num_cmp(0));

ENDDOCUMENT();




